hpnicfHgmp.name: hpnicfHgmp
hpnicfHgmp.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the hpnicfhgmp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hpnicfClusterObject.name: hpnicfClusterObject
hpnicfClusterObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the cluster operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hpnicfhgmpSetVLANSecurity.name: hpnicfhgmpSetVLANSecurity
hpnicfhgmpSetVLANSecurity.description: Configure whether to perform the VLAN check inside the cluster.

hpnicfhgmpHandShakeInterval.name: hpnicfhgmpHandShakeInterval
hpnicfhgmpHandShakeInterval.description: Handshaking interval of the cluster member switches.

hpnicfhgmpHandShakeHoldtime.name: hpnicfhgmpHandShakeHoldtime
hpnicfhgmpHandShakeHoldtime.description: Holdtime of administrator switch and member switch in the cluster.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberTableChange.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberTableChange
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberTableChange.description: Add 1 to the member list after it changes. The administrator checks if the value has changed. If not, he will not read the list once more.

hpnicfhgmpMemberDisconRate.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberDisconRate
hpnicfhgmpMemberDisconRate.description: Disconnection times of the member and administrator switches divided by member number times 1000.

hpnicfhgmpCmdClusterName.name: hpnicfhgmpCmdClusterName
hpnicfhgmpCmdClusterName.description: Cluster name of the administrator switch

hpnicfhgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP.name: hpnicfhgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP
hpnicfhgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP.description: The private management IP address of the administrator switch, which can not be modified after the cluster has been created.

hpnicfhgmpMngPriIpMask.name: hpnicfhgmpMngPriIpMask
hpnicfhgmpMngPriIpMask.description: The private management IP address mask assigned by the administrator switch, which cannot be modified after the cluster has been created.

hpnicfhgmpFtpServer.name: hpnicfhgmpFtpServer
hpnicfhgmpFtpServer.description: The cluster members can access the Ftp Server through the administrator switch, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hpnicfhgmpTftpServer.name: hpnicfhgmpTftpServer
hpnicfhgmpTftpServer.description: The cluster members can access the Tftp Server through the administrator switch, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hpnicfhgmpSnmpHost.name: hpnicfhgmpSnmpHost
hpnicfhgmpSnmpHost.description: The Snmp Host to send the cluster trap packets, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hpnicfhgmpLogHost.name: hpnicfhgmpLogHost
hpnicfhgmpLogHost.description: Log host of the cluster, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDeviceId.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDeviceId
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDeviceId.description: 4 bytes reserved as 0x0 + 6 bytes of MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberSerial.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberSerial
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberSerial.description: When adding member switch to the cluster, the administrator switch will assign an unique integer to identify it.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberIpAddr
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.description: The private IP addresses of the member switches for the communication inside the cluster.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberPassword.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberPassword
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberPassword.description: Member password for joining a cluster

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberPlatform.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberPlatform
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberPlatform.description: Set the hardware platform. A null string indicates the information does not exist in the device adjacency table.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberStatus.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberStatus
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberStatus.description: Member status on the administrator switch, use for displaying the network management status.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDisconCount.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDisconCount
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDisconCount.description: Count of inside communication disconnection between the member switch and the administrator switch.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime.description: Enrollment time of the member, measured in seconds.

hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberOperate.name: hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberOperate
hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberOperate.description: Operation indication field, indicates the operation of adding/removing a member by the network management agent.

hpnicfhgmpMemberResetTable.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberResetTable
hpnicfhgmpMemberResetTable.description: Reset a member switch in the cluster.

hpnicfhgmpMemberResetMAC.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberResetMAC
hpnicfhgmpMemberResetMAC.description: The management MAC address of the switch to be reset, which is the unique identifier of the switch.

hpnicfhgmpMemberEraseflash.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberEraseflash
hpnicfhgmpMemberEraseflash.description: Whether to erase the configuration file from the flash after resetting the switch. Read this node, cannotget(65535) will be returned.

hpnicfhgmpMemberfailure.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberfailure
hpnicfhgmpMemberfailure.description: When a cluster member failure, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hpnicfhgmpMemberRecover.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberRecover
hpnicfhgmpMemberRecover.description: When a cluster member recover, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hpnicfhgmpMemberStatusChange.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberStatusChange
hpnicfhgmpMemberStatusChange.description: When a cluster member status change, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hpnicfhgmpNetTopChange.name: hpnicfhgmpNetTopChange
hpnicfhgmpNetTopChange.description: When net topology of this cluster change, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hpnicfhgmpClusterMaxPoolNum.name: hpnicfhgmpClusterMaxPoolNum
hpnicfhgmpClusterMaxPoolNum.description: Max switch members that the cluster can support(include administrator switch).

hpnicfhgmpClusterCmdSwMac.name: hpnicfhgmpClusterCmdSwMac
hpnicfhgmpClusterCmdSwMac.description: The MAC address of administrator switch. It will be filled with zero when not be a member of cluster.

hpnicfhgmpClusterProtocolMac.name: hpnicfhgmpClusterProtocolMac
hpnicfhgmpClusterProtocolMac.description: Protocol MAC of HGMP protocol family. All multicast packets of this protocol family use this MAC as destination MAC.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistTable.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistTable
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistTable.description: Cluster switches white list table. White list topology is the topology which has been affirmed by network administrator in a cluster, and all devices in white list topology are recorded in this table. Against to white list table, black list table records the devices which are denied to join in cluster. Adding a black list device to white list table will cause a failure.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistDeviceId.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistDeviceId
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a white list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistSerial.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistSerial
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistSerial.description: When adding member switch to the cluster, the administrator switch will assign an unique integer to identify it. 0xffff means invalid value for this object.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistRowStatus.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistRowStatus
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbTable.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbTable
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbTable.description: Cluster switches white list neighboring information table. White list neighbor table records all neighbor devices for every white list device. In fact, white list neighbor table displays the whole white list topology.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbIndex.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbIndex
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbIndex.description: Index of a switch which is the neighbor of a white list switch identified by 'hgmpWhitelistDeviceId'.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a neighbor switch of a white list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistPortName.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistPortName
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistPortName.description: The name of the port which a white list switch connects to the neighbor specified by 'hgmpWhitelistNbIndex'.

hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbPortName.name: hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbPortName
hpnicfhgmpWhitelistNbPortName.description: The name of the port which a neighbor device connects to the white list switch specified by 'hgmpWhitelistDeviceId'.

hpnicfhgmpBlacklistTable.name: hpnicfhgmpBlacklistTable
hpnicfhgmpBlacklistTable.description: Cluster switches black list table. The black list table records all black list devices, and a device in black list is not permitted to join in any cluster.

hpnicfhgmpBlacklistDeviceId.name: hpnicfhgmpBlacklistDeviceId
hpnicfhgmpBlacklistDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a black list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hpnicfhgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId.name: hpnicfhgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId
hpnicfhgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating the access device of a black list switch. Tracing from a black list device to the cluster commander switch, the device which the black list switch directly connects to is the access device. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. 10 bytes of 0xff means invalid value for this object. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hpnicfhgmpBlacklistAccessPortName.name: hpnicfhgmpBlacklistAccessPortName
hpnicfhgmpBlacklistAccessPortName.description: The port which the access device connecting to the black list switch is named access port, the object returns the access port name. An empty string means invalid value for this object.

hpnicfhgmpBlacklistRowStatus.name: hpnicfhgmpBlacklistRowStatus
hpnicfhgmpBlacklistRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortTable.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortTable
hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortTable.description: This table contains port number for different network protocols on each member switch. The port number can be used to access a specified member switch with specified protocol and private IP address.

hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortEntry.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortEntry
hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortEntry.description: Information about a specified member private port entry. The indexes of the entry are hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberDevId and hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProto, which indicate entries in the table.

hpnicfhgmpMemberDevId.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberDevId
hpnicfhgmpMemberDevId.description: Unique identifier indicating the switch in cluster. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address.

hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProto.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProto
hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProto.description: The index of this table. Each instance value of this object corresponds to a different protocol.

hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr
hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr.description: It describes the hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProtocol object value. For example, it is 'SNMP' when hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProtocol value is 1.

hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortNum.name: hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortNum
hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortNum.description: The private port number of member switch, used by specified hpnicfhgmpMemberPriPortProto. By using the private IP address, specified protocol and port number, other devices outside cluster can access member switch. The private IP address can be acquired by reading hpnicfhgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.

hpnicfStackObject.name: hpnicfStackObject
hpnicfStackObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the stack operations, which is used on lanswitch products.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberTableChange.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberTableChange
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberTableChange.description: Change identifier of the stack member table.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDisconRate.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDisconRate
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDisconRate.description: Disconnection rate of the stack member switches.

hpnicfhgmpMainLanswitchFlag.name: hpnicfhgmpMainLanswitchFlag
hpnicfhgmpMainLanswitchFlag.description: The status of the local switch in the stack.

hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolStartIP.name: hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolStartIP
hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolStartIP.description: The first address of the management IP network segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolLength.name: hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolLength
hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolLength.description: The length of the management IP segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolMask.name: hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolMask
hpnicfhgmpStackIpPoolMask.description: The mask of the management IP segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDeviceId.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDeviceId
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDeviceId.description: 2 bytes address type of the switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a hexadecimal number string.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberSerial.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberSerial
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberSerial.description: When adding a member switch to the stack, the master switch will assign an unique integer to identify it.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberIpAddr.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberIpAddr
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberIpAddr.description: The private member IP address for the communication inside the stack.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberPassword.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberPassword
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberPassword.description: Member password for joining a stack.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberPlatform.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberPlatform
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberPlatform.description: Set the hardware platform. A null string indicates the information does not exist in the device adjacency table.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberStatus.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberStatus
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberStatus.description: Member status on the master switch, use for displaying the network management status.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDisconCount.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDisconCount
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberDisconCount.description: Count of inside communication disconnection between the member switch and the master switch.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberEnrollTime.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberEnrollTime
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberEnrollTime.description: Enrollment time of the member, measured in seconds.

hpnicfhgmpStackRole.name: hpnicfhgmpStackRole
hpnicfhgmpStackRole.description: This switch's role status in stack.

hpnicfhgmpStackMaxPoolNum.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMaxPoolNum
hpnicfhgmpStackMaxPoolNum.description: Max switch members in one stack that the switch support (include main switch).

hpnicfhgmpStackMainSwMac.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMainSwMac
hpnicfhgmpStackMainSwMac.description: The MAC address of main switch. It will be 00.00.00 when not be a member of stack.

hpnicfNDPObject.name: hpnicfNDPObject
hpnicfNDPObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the ndp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hpnicfNDPHelloTimer.name: hpnicfNDPHelloTimer
hpnicfNDPHelloTimer.description: NDP packet transmission interval, measured in seconds.

hpnicfNDPAgingTime.name: hpnicfNDPAgingTime
hpnicfNDPAgingTime.description: How long the NDP information of the local switch can be hold in the adjacent switch, measured in seconds.

hpnicfNDPChange.name: hpnicfNDPChange
hpnicfNDPChange.description: Change identifier of the Neighbor table

hpnicfNDPPortTable.name: hpnicfNDPPortTable
hpnicfNDPPortTable.description: Configure to enable/disable the interface NDP of the switch.

hpnicfNDPIfIndex.name: hpnicfNDPIfIndex
hpnicfNDPIfIndex.description: Unique identifier of an interface of the device.

hpnicfNDPPortStatus.name: hpnicfNDPPortStatus
hpnicfNDPPortStatus.description: If it is enable, the device will send and receive the NDP packets via the interface. To disable the NDP function on the interface, set the entry as false.

hpnicfNDPPortNbTable.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbTable
hpnicfNDPPortNbTable.description: NDP neighbor information on the switch.

hpnicfNDPPortNbDeviceId.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbDeviceId
hpnicfNDPPortNbDeviceId.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hpnicfNDPPortNbPortName.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbPortName
hpnicfNDPPortNbPortName.description: Unique identifier of a port. A null string indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NDP packet. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hpnicfNDPPortNbDeviceName.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbDeviceName
hpnicfNDPPortNbDeviceName.description: Device name. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hpnicfNDPPortNbProductVer.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbProductVer
hpnicfNDPPortNbProductVer.description: Product version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hpnicfNDPPortNbHardVer.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbHardVer
hpnicfNDPPortNbHardVer.description: Hardware version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hpnicfNDPPortNbBootromVer.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbBootromVer
hpnicfNDPPortNbBootromVer.description: Bootrom version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hpnicfNDPPortNbSoftVer.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbSoftVer
hpnicfNDPPortNbSoftVer.description: Software version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hpnicfNDPPortNbAgingtime.name: hpnicfNDPPortNbAgingtime
hpnicfNDPPortNbAgingtime.description: How long the NDP information of the local switch can be hold in the adjacent switch, measured in seconds.

hpnicfNTDPObject.name: hpnicfNTDPObject
hpnicfNTDPObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the ntdp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCollectTopTime.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCollectTopTime
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCollectTopTime.description: Topology collection interval of the administrator switch of the cluster, measured in minutes.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPHopRange.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPHopRange
hpnicfhgmpNTDPHopRange.description: Range of the topology collection of the administrator switch

hpnicfhgmpNTDPRun.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPRun
hpnicfhgmpNTDPRun.description: Enable/Disable the NTDP function on the switch.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPPortDelay.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPPortDelay
hpnicfhgmpNTDPPortDelay.description: Set the delay to forward the topology request via the ports, measured in milliseconds.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPHopDelay.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPHopDelay
hpnicfhgmpNTDPHopDelay.description: Set the delay to forward the topology request from every hop, measured in milliseconds.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration
hpnicfhgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration.description: Duration of the latest overall topology collection, a performance count measured in seconds.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheChange.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheChange
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheChange.description: Add 1 when the device table changes. The network administrator will check if it has changed before accessing the table. If it has not changed, he will not access again.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTOPTableChange.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTOPTableChange
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTOPTableChange.description: Add 1 when the topology table changes. The network administrator will check if it has changed before accessing the table. If it has not changed, he will not access again.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceTable.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceTable
hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceTable.description: Enable/Disable the NTDP on the switch port.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex
hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex.description: Unique identifier an interface of the device.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable
hpnicfhgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable.description: If it is true, the device will send and receive the NTDP packets via the interface. To disable the NTDP function on the interface, set the entry as false.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheTable.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheTable
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheTable.description: Access the information about the switch from the topology table.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex.description: Our NTDP information is saved in the HASH table on the administrator switch. Using DeviceID as index will lead to the comparison of a large amount of character strings, which puts too many burdens on the administrator switch. A HAHSIndex is added to reduce the character string comparison to the least range.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheClusterName.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheClusterName
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheClusterName.description: Name of the cluster including the device.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole.description: Cluster role of the current device, which can be a administrator switch (0x01), member switch(0x02), backup switch(0x03), candidate switch(0x10) or an independent switch (incapable of cluster member) (0x11).

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities.description: The capabilities of the device. FF indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NTDP packet.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheVersion.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheVersion
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheVersion.description: The version information of the corresponding device. A null string indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NTDP packet.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCachePlatform.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCachePlatform
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCachePlatform.description: Hardware platform. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NTDP packet.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN
hpnicfhgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN.description: The management VLAN ID of the device.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopTable.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopTable
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopTable.description: Access the topology structure collected by the NTDP.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopHashIndex.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopHashIndex
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopHashIndex.description: Our NTDP information is saved in the HASH table on the administrator switch. Using DeviceID as index will lead to the comparison of a large amount of character strings, which puts too many burdens on the administrator switch. A HAHSIndex is added to reduce the character string comparison to the least range.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex.description: Edge index of this entry in the data structure.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort.description: The number of the first port of a topology edge. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex.description: The full-duplex status of the first port on a topology edge.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed.description: The speed of the first port on a topology edge.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort.description: The number of the last port of a topology edge. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus.name: hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus
hpnicfhgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus.description: In STP or RSTP, it describes link status according to port STP steady status. In MSTP it describes STP steady status of the instance which management VLAN belongs to. Either 'hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort' or 'hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort' STP steady status is 'blocking', this object is 'blocking', otherwise is 'forwarding'. If STP or MSTP is disabled, this object is 'forwarding'.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberfailure.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberfailure
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberfailure.description: When a stack member failure, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberRecover.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberRecover
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberRecover.description: When a stack member Recover, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hpnicfhgmpStackMemberStatusChange.name: hpnicfhgmpStackMemberStatusChange
hpnicfhgmpStackMemberStatusChange.description: When a stack member status change, send a snmp trap to the network management.
